{
  "text": "As voltage inputs and ADC elements are shared across the filters, analog and digital scaling stages would be required. Different ADC designs leads to additional area, power consumption, and higher design times [CITATION_1] . Figure 4 . Simplified version of a quantized graph using straight through estimator. Forward passes are quantized following the desired method. During Back-Propagation stages (dotted) the gradient computation do not consider quantization blocks.",
